1. e4 e5 2. d4 exd4 3. c3 d5 4. exd5 Nf6 5. cxd4 Nxd5 6. Nc3 Bb4 7. Ne2
{ An unfortunate decision by White, which immediately hands over the advantage to Black. }
7... O-O 8. a3 Ba5 9. Bd2 Nc6 10. Qb3
{ This unfortunate move decides the fate of the game.   10.Nxd5  was slightly better but Black remains on top after  10...Qxd5  11.Bxa5  Nxa5∓ }
10... Be6 11. Qxb7
{ White shows greed in a position where he should have done everything to catch up in development and secure the King. The punishment will be severe! }
11... Qd7 12. Qa6 Rab8 13. O-O-O
{ One must admire White's bold style, but the sad reality is that this is just castling right into death. }
13... Rb6 14. Qd3 Bf5 15. Qc4 Bxc3
{ 15...Rfb8!  would have been, of course, the right move, not only because it is stylish, but also because it obeys our great friend Yasser's demand: 'Bring all the boys to the party!'  16.Qxd5  Rxb2  17.Qxd7  Rc2 }
16. Bxc3 Rfb8 { This still seals the deal. } 17. Ng3 Bg6 18. Bd3 Na5 19. Qa2
Nxc3 20. bxc3 Bxd3 21. Rxd3 Qb5 22. Rf3 Nc4 23. a4 Qg5+ *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "3) Center Game"]
[Black "Center Game 2.d4 exd4 3.Qxd4 Nc6 4.Qa4"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. d4 { The Center Game kicks off as if it were a Danish Gambit... }
2... exd4 3. Qxd4
{ ...but then it takes a sharp turn towards a different direction! As mentioned, this looks mostly like a reversed Scandinavian. }
3... Nc6 4. Qa4
{ This move really builds on the Scandinavian vibes. Note that while e4 certainly allows White faster development, it also shuts the queen's path along the 4th rank. }
4... Bc5 5. Nf3 d6
{ Black is preparing for the annoying ...Bd7 move, creating a discovered attack on the queen. }
6. Bb5 Bd7 7. O-O Nf6 8. Nc3 a6 9. Bxc6
{ 9.Bd3??  b5  10.Qb3  Na5-+  demonstrates the problems with the queen's placement. }
9... Bxc6
{ Black stands better with the bishop pair. White still needs to play several moves with the queen to find a spot where she can remain unpestered. ...O-O followed by ...Re8 is the best way to proceed. }
*

