[White "3) Center Game"]
[Black "Center Game 2.d4 exd4 3.Qxd4 Nc6 4.Qd1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. d4 { The Center Game kicks off as if it were a Danish Gambit... }
2... exd4 3. Qxd4
{ ...but then it takes a sharp turn towards a different direction! As mentioned, this looks mostly like a reversed Scandinavian. }
3... Nc6 4. Qd1
{ This variation looks like a Four Knight Scotch that went horribly wrong for White. }
4... Nf6 5. Nc3 Bb4
{ Just like in the Four Knights Scotch, we develop with a tempo, creating a pin and hitting e4. }
6. Bd3 d5
{ As usual, the break in the center is the most natural way to further increase our lead in development. }
7. exd5 Qxd5 { Utilising the pin, we bring all our pieces into the game. } 8.
Nf3 Bg4 9. O-O Bxc3 10. bxc3 O-O-O
{ Black has a marvellous position. The black army is developed harmoniously, whereas White is struggling to even complete development. The pressure on f3 is very annoying and Black has simple, yet very effective moves to build the position, such as ...Ne5 and ...Rhe8. }
