[White "4) Bishop's Opening"]
[Black "Introduction"]
[Result "*"]

1. --
{ The Bishop's Opening is another historic artifact as it was played by many masters of the distant past including the Lucena, the Ruy Lopez, and the Philidor.   In the second part of the 1900s Bent Larsen and the Australian legend, Ian Rogers played it with notable success. Depending on how Black responds, games often transpose to the Italian or even into the King’s Gambit.   Our treatment is going to be unique, leading to early fights for the control of the middle. }
*

