[White "4) Bishop's Opening"]
[Black "2.Bc4 Nf6 3.Nf3 Nxe4 "]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 { This move aptly introduces the 'Bishop's Opening'. } 2... Nf6
{ This is best and is also in sync with our other lines. After  3.Nc3  Nxe4  we transpose to our Vienna lines, which we will examinehere. }
3. Nf3
{ Shockingly, this mistake is the second most popular move in the Lichess database! }
3... Nxe4 4. Nxe5 d5
{ Black is already ahead due to the free tempo scored on the c4 Bishop. } 5.
Be2 Bd6 6. d4 Nd7
{ And we have a much more preferable version of a Petroff main line with an extra tempo and a misplaced white Bishop on e2 @@StartBracket@@in the Petroff it is on d3@@EndBracket@@. }
*

