1. e4 e5 2. Nc3
{ This move introduces the Vienna game. The most common idea behind the setup is to play a 'delayed king's gambit'. }
2... Nf6
{ 2...Nc6  is also known here but the text is the most challenging. Black is preparing the d7-d5 counterpunch. }
3. Bc4 Nxe4
{ This pseudo-sacrifice is a very common motif in many e4-e5 openings, and certainly one to remember! }
4. Qh5 { This move is by far White's best, threatening both e5 and f7. } 4...
Nd6 5. Bb3 Nc6
{ This is the so-called 'Dracula-Frankenstein Variation', which is a great example of how even our beautiful game is not exempt from the odd bit of kitsch.   This artificial name attempts to refer to the bloodthirsty nature of the line, which is precisely why I recommend it.   This variation is certainly not for the faint-hearted and so I recommend here an alternative, right out of the books of the formerly mentioned Chicken Chess Club. }
6. Nb5 { White now has a dangerous attack against f7. } 6... g6 7. Qf3 f5 8.
Qd5
{ White relentlessly chases after the mate threat on f7 and indeed, now something has to give. }
8... Qe7
{ A remarkable idea! Black is willing to give up a rook in order to grab the initiative and dominate the center! Fun times! }
9. Nxc7+ Kd8 10. Nxa8 b6
{ At first sight, Black is completely lost with the King in the middle and a whole rook down.   However, equally importantly, the initiative has completely shifted and now it is White who will be under substantial pressure! }
11. d3 Bb7 12. h4 { A cheeky sortie by White, Bg5 is the obvious threat. }
12... f4
{ This move shuts the c1 Bishop out of the game entirely. Now we are threatening to win a Queen with Nd4! }
13. Qf3 Nd4 14. Qh3 Bh6
{ Black completes development of the minor pieces and is now threatening to blast the center open against the white King with e5-e4. }
15. c3 Re8 { This sensational idea would make Morphy proud! } 16. cxd4
{ Leads to another variation that London and Caro-Kann players can only dream of! }
16... exd4+ 17. Be3 dxe3 18. fxe3 f3 { With a deadly attack again for Black. }
