1. e4 e5 2. Nc3
{ This move introduces the Vienna game. The most common idea behind the setup is to play a 'delayed king's gambit'. }
2... Nf6
{ 2...Nc6  is also known here but the text is the most challenging. Black is preparing the d7-d5 counterpunch. }
3. g3
{ This move hopes to steer the game towards positional pastures, however, once again, we have different ideas in mind! }
3... d5 4. exd5 c6
{ This is our key move. The idea is to play a reverse Danish Gambit, where White's g3 move is more of a hindrance than a help. }
5. dxc6 Nxc6 6. Bg2 Bg4
{ As so often in this course, here too, our motto is 'pedal to the metal'. The idea is to exploit the weakness of the light squares. }
7. Nge2 Nd4
{ The b7 pawn is fishbait, and grabbing it has mortal consequences! } 8. Bxb7
Rc8
{ A sensational effect: The rook moves from being en prise to being en prise again! But now we have a threat: Rxc3! }
9. O-O Rxc3 10. dxc3 Nxe2+ 11. Kh1 { 11.Kg2  Nf4+-+ } 11... Nxg3+ *

