9. Qe1 Qh5 10. Kd1
{ Incredibly, this line was employed twice by Nakamura, but even that does not make it good... }
10... Bxf3+ 11. gxf3 Qxf3+ 12. Be2 Qd5
{ And Black stands much better, as White will have a constant problem with securing the king.   O-O-O is our plan, putting even more pressure on White along the central files. }
