{ White's most ambitious and aggressive move, that defends the Knight on g5 and challenges the center at the same time.   Now the game becomes very sharp and any mistake may be the last one for both sides! }
8... exd4 9. Qxd4
{ This innocuous move demonstrates really well the dangers lurking in the position. }
9... Qe7+ 10. Be3 O-O-O
{ Don't fall for the absurd claim that the black King is weak and exposed. It is not!   Actually, it is White who is in trouble, partly because of the uncastled @@StartBracket@@unsafe@@EndBracket@@ King! }
11. Bxc6 Bxc6 12. Qxa7 Nf4
{ And Black is completely winning! @@StartBracket@@The engine gives -7.1@@EndBracket@@   Other than the hanging Knight on g5, Nxg2+ is also terminal. In contrast, White's Qa6 check is refuted by the simple Bb7. }
