{ Unfortunately @@StartBracket@@since the queen is not on the trappable g7 square in this line, unlike previous lines, we must prevent the knight fork on f7@@EndBracket@@ we have to play this ugly move in order to prepare O-O-O.   On the other hand, White's position is not exactly picture-perfect either... }
15. Na3 O-O-O 16. Nc4 Ba8
{ This prophylactic move retains the powerful Bishop on the long diagonal.   This chaotic mess is exactly the kind of imbalance we aim for. Although our king's position is compromised, White does not have the means to exploit it.   Our future plans are based on drumming up an attack against the White king with Qf5 - Bc5 etc. }
