{ This Knight sortie is the Belgrade Gambit, a tricky but overall harmless variation. }
5... Nb4
{ The engine's top choice and in many ways the most annoying response. Black immediately wants to eliminate the pesky intruder on d5. }
6. Nxd4
{ Is a trickster variation with many deadly traps, so we really need to be precise here! }
6... Nbxd5 7. exd5 Nxd5
{ Black has gained a pawn but now White gets some intiative and we need to defend very accurately. }
8. Nf5 Ne7
{ This counter-intuitive withdrawal is actually the best move here, immediately challenging the well-placed f5 Knight.   Note that after  8...Nf6??  9.Qe2+!  Be7  10.Nxg7+  Kf8  11.Bh6  Black is dead lost! }
9. Bg5 { White's only hope to maintain the initiative. } 9... f6 10. Bxf6
