Qh5+ Ng6 12. O-O-O c6
{ This is the last tricky move in the line. The idea is to neutralize the upcoming Bc4 with d7-d5.   The immediate  12...d5?  is too premature due to:  13.Rxd5!  Qxd5  14.Ng7+ }
13. Bc4 d5 14. Rhe1+ Kf7
{ And White's attack has run out of steam. Our plan is to play Bxf5 followed by Bd6, consolidating our extra piece. }
