{ This move introduces the Four Knights Scotch, whereas  4.Bb5  is the Four Knights Spanish. }
4... exd4 5. Nd5
{ This Knight sortie is the Belgrade Gambit, a tricky but overall harmless variation. }
5... Nb4
{ The engine's top choice and in many ways the most annoying response. Black immediately wants to eliminate the pesky intruder on d5. }
6. Bc4 Nbxd5 7. exd5 Bb4+
{ This check solves all of our problems instantly, as now we are good to castle, and we can also trade pieces with a subsequent Qe7+ }
8. Bd2 Qe7+ 9. Qe2 O-O
{ I prefer this move over the trades on e2 and d2 which resolve the tension too soon. }
10. Qxe7 Bxe7 11. Nxd4
{ After  11.O-O  Bc5  Black has a preferable position. We simply aim to complete development with d6-Bd7. }
11... Bc5 12. Be3 Ng4
