{ White is up a pawn with an intact pawn structure on their side, but there is not a lot of joy in it. The Knights are clumsy and the e4 pawn is still hanging. }
12. Bg5 Qe8 13. Bxf6 Rxf6 14. Ng3 Qf7
{ And the World Champion had a very pleasant position which he followed up with Be6 and Re8 in Anand - Carlsen 2008, Bilbao. }
