{ The Schliemann @@StartBracket@@also known as Jaenisch@@EndBracket@@ Gambit is a bold choice to contest one of the most classical and respected chess openings.   Apart from the fact that this line is sharp and confrontational, it also allows players to reduce their workload by eliminating a large number of side variations, such as the exchange Spanish, the early d4 lines, and the early d3 variations, etc. }
4. d3
{ The most popular choice on club level. This move, however, is a tad too timid and passive to be a serious attempt at refuting the Schliemann. }
4... fxe4 { This capture is actually a must as exf5 was a threat! } 5. dxe4 Nf6
6. O-O Bc5
{ This move introduces one of the important themes in the Schliemann: Black happily parts with a pawn @@StartBracket@@or two!@@EndBracket@@ in order to obtain the Bishop pair and some initiative! }
7. Nc3
