7... d6 8. Bg5 O-O
{ One thing we need to note here is that we certainly should not be afraid of Nd5 as far as the pressure on f6 is concerned. Retaking with the pawn is totally fine! }
9. Nd5 Kh8
{ A nice prophylactic move, preparing for Rg8, should White go ahead with the trade on f6. }
10. Nxf6 gxf6 11. Bh6 Rg8
{ And it is Black @@StartBracket@@of course!@@EndBracket@@ who has the real attacking prospects on the kingside! }
