{ The Schliemann @@StartBracket@@also known as Jaenisch@@EndBracket@@ Gambit is a bold choice to contest one of the most classical and respected chess openings.   Apart from the fact that this line is sharp and confrontational, it also allows players to reduce their workload by eliminating a large number of side variations, such as the exchange Spanish, the early d4 lines, and the early d3 variations, etc. }
