1. e4 e5 2. Qf3 { Is an alternative version of the  2.Qh5  nonsense. } 2... Nf6
3. Bc4 c6
{ Similarly to the Bishop Game, here too, we go for ...d5 and central control! }
4. Nc3 b5
{ The following sequence pushes the white pieces around and also gains territory on the queenside. }
5. Bb3 b4 6. Na4 d5 { Mission accomplished, we conquered the middle! } 7. d3
Be7 8. Ne2 O-O 9. O-O Be6
{ And Black has a more harmonious development and thus a better position, ...Nbd7-...Qc7 is a good way to continue. }
