1. e4 e5 2. Qh5
{ This move is setting up the classic cheapo with  2...g6??  3.Qxe5+   This is also a way to go for the Scholar's Mate. }
2... Nc6 3. Bc4 g6 4. Qf3
{ White insists on playing kindergarten style, but then again, recently the MAN himself, Magnus Carlsen tried it against GM Dominguez.   Then again, Magnus often likes to play for memes! 😊 }
4... Nf6 { Stopping the mate and developing a new piece. } 5. c3
{ Is strongly met by: } 5... Na5
{ Kicking the Bishop and thus, preparing the d5 central break! } 6. Be2 d5
{ 'When chess is played well, it is played in the CENTAH!' -said a known Chessable author and so we obey! 😊 }
7. d3 Bg7 8. Bg5 Be6
{ Black is clearly better. We have completed our development, and control of the center.   In contrast, the White Knights have no real future and the Queen is awkward on f3. }
